"authors": ["Bob AminAzad", "Adam Martinetti"],
"date_published": "March 2024",
"abstract": "This article discusses Cloudflare's latest machine learning model (ML v8) that is designed to detect and mitigate residential proxy attacks. The new model uses a combination of network latency-based features, behavioral signals, and global aggregates to accurately classify requests from residential proxies on a per-request basis. The article also provides case studies demonstrating the effectiveness of ML v8 in detecting previously missed attacks and improving detection for bots from cloud providers.",
"keywords": ["Machine Learning", "AI", "Proxying", "Bots", "Bot Management", "Application Services"],
"body": [
{
"paragraphs": [
