{"name": "SpellVault's Evolution",
"children": [
    {
        "name": "Introduction",
        "children": [
            {
                "name": "Background",
                "content": "SpellVault is a no-code platform that allows users to build apps using large language models (LLMs). It was initially designed for creating LLM apps, but has evolved over time."
            },
            {
                "name": "Early Capabilities",
                "content": "SpellVault started with basic capabilities like one-off information retrieval from the Knowledge Vault or user plugins. Users could toggle features through simple checkboxes in the user interface."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Expanding Capabilities",
        "children": [
            {
                "name": "Additional Features",
                "content": "Over time, SpellVault introduced new capabilities like Python code execution and internal repository search. These functionalities were integrated into the core PromptBuilder class."
            },
            {
                "name": "Unified Tools Framework",
                "content": "As SpellVault moved towards making agentic behavior more natural, these scattered capabilities were consolidated into a unified framework called 'Native Tools'. These Native Tools, along with user plugins, formed a comprehensive collection of tools that LLMs could dynamically invoke at runtime."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Shifting to an Agentic Framework",
        "children": [
            {
                "name": "MCP Integration",
                "content": "SpellVault was adapted to function as an MCP service, enabling it to interact seamlessly with other agents and tools in the agentic ecosystem."
            },
            {
                "name": "Impact",
                "content": "By exposing both apps and RAG through MCP, SpellVault shifted from being a self-contained platform to becoming an interoperable service provider. Users still benefit from the no-code simplicity inside SpellVault, but their output is now usable by other agents and tools outside of it."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "Conclusion",
        "content": "SpellVault's evolution shows how a platform can adapt with the AI landscape while staying true to its original mission of making powerful technology accessible to everyone. It has steadily expanded into an agentic platform, supporting more sophisticated agentic behaviors without compromising its original goal."
    }
]}

