          "sender": "Doctolib Agentic RAG Architecture Analysis",
          "text": "The Doctolib Agentic RAG Architecture is a system that combines Natural Language Understanding (NLU), Applicative Intent, and Agentic Capabilities to create a comprehensive and efficient solution for natural language interaction. The key components of the architecture are as follows: \n\n1. NLU Layer: This layer uses LLMs to understand human language effectively and interpret user's intentions and requests.\n2. Applicative Intent Layer: This layer translates the user's intent into a format that the system can comprehend and execute with the goal to minimize hallucinations.\n3. Agentic Capabilities: These capabilities bridge the gap between natural language understanding and the system’s ability to take action, enabling seamless communication between the user and the system.\n\nThe potential benefits of this architecture include a smooth and meaningful user experience by accurately understanding user intent and providing relevant and actionable responses. It has the potential to revolutionize various domains such as virtual assistants, chatbots, customer support systems, and more."
